- **Consistent Icon Button and Tooltip/Popover UI for Admin Pages**
  - Use `.icon-btn` (plus `.icon-btn-edit`, `.icon-btn-delete`, `.icon-btn-upload`) for all action icons (edit, delete, upload, etc.) for consistent size, color, and hover/focus effects.
  - **For delete actions, always use `FaTrashAlt` from `react-icons/fa` for the correct grilled/trash-can look.**
  - Use `.admin-tooltip` for all mouse-over popovers that show detailed info (e.g., user or event details in a table row).
  - Use `.admin-tooltip-table` for the inner table to ensure cell borders, padding, and compact text.
  - Ensures all admin action icons and tooltips/popovers are visually consistent, accessible, and easy to scan.

**How to use (Icons):**
```jsx
import { FaEdit, FaTrashAlt, FaUpload } from 'react-icons/fa';
<button className="icon-btn icon-btn-edit"><FaEdit /></button>
<button className="icon-btn icon-btn-delete"><FaTrashAlt /></button>
<button className="icon-btn icon-btn-upload"><FaUpload /></button>
```
- `.icon-btn` for base styling; add a modifier for color/hover.
- Use on `<button>`, `<a>`, or `<span>` as needed.
- **Do not use `FaTrash` for delete; always use `FaTrashAlt` for the grilled look.**

**How to use (Tooltip/Popover):**
```jsx
// Place a note above the table:
<div className="mb-2 text-sm text-blue-700 bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded px-4 py-2">
  Mouse over the first 3 columns to see the full details about the item. Use the × button to close the tooltip once you have viewed the details.
</div>

// In your table, only show the tooltip on mouse over of the first 3 columns (e.g., Title, Type, Preview):
<td
  onMouseEnter={...}
  onMouseLeave={...}
>
  ...
</td>

// Tooltip markup:
<div className="admin-tooltip">
  <table className="admin-tooltip-table">
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <th>Field</th>
        <td>Value</td>
      </tr>
      {/* ...more rows... */}
    </tbody>
  </table>
</div>
```
- `.admin-tooltip` gives you a white background, border, rounded corners, shadow, and padding.
- `.admin-tooltip` now also includes `max-height: 60vh`, `overflow-y: auto`, and `padding-bottom: 16px` to ensure the tooltip never overflows the viewport and always has padding at the bottom. This is handled globally in `src/app/globals.css`—no inline styles are needed.
- `.admin-tooltip-table` gives the table full width, cell borders, and compact text.
- **Show the tooltip only on mouse over of the first 3 columns, not the whole row.**
- Place a clear note above the table to inform users about the tooltip behavior.
- Use for any mouse-over or click-to-view popover in admin tables.

